  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-04-06 02:09 UTC \u2014 [P2: Smart Entry] 191-Trade Deep Analysis: Three Filter Upgrades Identified\n\n**Task:** Quantitative analysis of all 191 logged trades in confidence_outcomes.jsonl to find actionable parameter improvements for the PM smart entry bot.\n\n**Finding:** Three high-signal edges discovered from the data:\n\n1. **Bias score sweet spot is 45-65, NOT 25-70 (current range)**\n   - |bias| 25-35: 53.8% WR (39 trades) \u2014 barely above coin flip\n   - |bias| 35-45: 48.8% WR (41 trades) \u2014 LOSING after fees\n   - |bias| 45-55: 58.3% WR (72 trades) \u2014 solid\n   - |bias| 55-65: 83.3% WR (18 trades) \u2014 **MONSTER edge**\n   - |bias| 65-70: 42.9% WR (7 trades) \u2014 overcrowded, reversal trap\n   - Current thresholds: bias_threshold=25, max_bias=70. This lets in 80 trades (42%) that are at or below breakeven.\n\n2. **OBI > 0.5 is a kill zone: 33.3% WR vs 75% when OBI \u2264 0.5**\n   - OBI [-1.0, -0.5): 83.3% WR (6 trades)\n   - OBI [-0.5, 0.0): 60.0% WR (5 trades)\n   - OBI [0.0, 0.5): 80.0% WR (10 trades)\n   - OBI [0.5, 1.0): 33.3% WR (6 trades) \u2014 **strong buy-side imbalance = trap**\n   - Sample is small (27 trades with OBI data) but signal is extreme.\n\n3. **v5a BLOCK tag = 25% WR but trades STILL EXECUTE**\n   - v5a_tag is logged at line 201-202 of trading_bot.py but never used as an actual filter\n   - v5a=PASS: 71.4% WR (14 trades) vs v5a=BLOCK: 25.0% WR (4 trades)\n   - The v5a check (`abs(bias_score) >= 45`) aligns with finding #1 above\n\n4. **Entry price 0.54-0.56 is a dead zone: 40% WR**\n   - Sweet spot is 0.50-0.54 (61.4-61.5% WR)\n   - Current max_price=0.535 already handles this well\n\n5. **Last 30 trades: 70% WR** \u2014 recent performance trending up, bot parameters are improving\n\n6. **Hour analysis (with enriched data, n=27):** Hour 11 = 80% (10 trades), Hour 12 = 66.7% (12 trades). Hours 19-20 underperforming (50%/0% but tiny samples).\n\n**My thinking:** The single biggest leak is low-bias trades (|bias| < 45). These represent ~42% of all trades and collectively lose money. The v5a tag already identifies this but was never wired as a filter \u2014 it's just a log annotation. The OBI > 0.5 filter would catch another subset of losers. These two filters together would have blocked ~45 of the 83 losses while keeping most of the 108 wins.\n\n**Decision:** Three changes to implement (in priority order):\n1. **Raise bias_threshold from 25 \u2192 45** \u2014 this is the single most impactful change. Cuts 80 low-WR trades, keeps the 97 high-WR trades. Expected WR jumps from 56.5% \u2192 ~63%.\n2. **Add OBI > 0.5 as a hard block** \u2014 small sample but the signal is extreme (33% WR). Worth implementing as a filter with logging.\n3. **Lower max_bias from 70 \u2192 65** \u2014 the 65-70 bucket is 42.9% WR. Extreme bias = reversal territory.\n\nNOT implementing yet (waiting for more data):\n- v5a as hard filter (it's equivalent to bias_threshold=45, so change #1 covers this)\n- Hour 19/20 removal (sample too small at 5 trades)\n\n*",
